"{\"uid\": \"awfulannouncing.com-olympics-closing-ceremony-revised-several-times.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Awful Announcing The good news?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 32, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Awful\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"The good news\", \"from\": 17, \"to\": 30}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a week's worth of controversy, nobody seems to be talking about the opening ceremony at the 2024 Paris Olympics anymore.\", \"from\": 33, \"to\": 159, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a week's worth\", \"from\": 39, \"to\": 53}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 68}, {\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 76}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 123}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bad news?\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bad news\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sunday's closing ceremony could very well change that.\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 228, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday's closing ceremony\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after the opening ceremony was criticized by many for imagery that was construed as anti-religion and anti-American, the executive director of the closing ceremony is determined to not let his presentation suffer the same fate.\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 240, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"imagery\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 295}, {\"ngram\": \"the executive director\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"his presentation\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"the same fate\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, Thierry Reboul says that he's already revised the closing ceremony multiple times - \\\"umpteenth\\\" times, to be exact - after receiving death threats following the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.042989354243681e-17, \"text\": \"Thierry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Augustin_Thierry\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 469}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"death threats\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You have to live with it and file a complaint, show that you will not let yourself be pushed around or intimidated,\\\" Reboultold The Guardianof the death threats.\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a complaint\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"The Guardianof\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But they forced us to have to reread the entire show for the umpteenth time to be sure that there is no possible misinterpretation, that we are not made to say what we do not want to say.\\\"\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire show\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"the umpteenth time\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"no possible misinterpretation\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most controversial scene from the opening ceremony centered on what many interpreted as a reimagining of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" featuring scantily clad drag performers.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3476640889529e-17, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most controversial scene\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"a reimagining\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"scantily clad drag performers\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics organizers apologized following the outcry, but insisted the scene - which was titled \\\"festivity\\\" - wasn't intended to mock \\\"The Last Supper\\\" but was rather a depiction of Dionysus, the Greek god of wine.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.037467898328625e-17, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics organizers\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"the outcry\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"festivity\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"a depiction\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"the Greek god\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The idea was to create a big pagan party in link with the God of Mount Olympus - and you will never find in me, or in my work, any desire of mocking anyone,\\\" the ceremony's artistic director, Thomas Jolly, said,according to CBS News.\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.9999313578509168, \"rank\": 6.74860094571127e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"score\": 0.9935238220809319, \"rank\": 0.006518392100059164, \"text\": \"CBS News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The idea\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"a big pagan party\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"link\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"the God\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"Mount Olympus\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"my work\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony's artistic director\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless of the intent, the messaging clearly did not land with many, sparkingyet another battle in the ongoing culture war, especially in the United States.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.99997953026637, \"rank\": 2.0465661264442493e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the intent\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"the messaging\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"another battle\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1743}, {\"ngram\": \"the ongoing culture war\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Understandably, the event's organizers are taking extra precautions to make sure the closing ceremony does not elicit a similar reaction - at least from those whodidn't swear off watching the rest of the Olympicsaltogether following the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 2059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event's organizers\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"extra precautions\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"a similar reaction\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2001}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympicsaltogether\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"[The Guardian] Ben Axelrod is a veteran of the sports media landscape, having most recently worked for NBC's Cleveland affiliate, WKYC.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2081, \"end\": 2088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dylan_Axelrod\", \"score\": 0.9976694010381154, \"rank\": 0.002336043291461842, \"text\": \"Axelrod\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dylan_Axelrod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dylan_Axelrod\"}, {\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.7183648214498544, \"rank\": 0.31681691159690667, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"score\": 0.9995357318069011, \"rank\": 0.00031904509703026523, \"text\": \"Cleveland\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"